{:proof/problem-id "apm-a92J02", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (plan and alignment explicitly reference the measurable functions \\(f_n\\), the limit \\(f\\), the measure \\(μ\\), and convergence in measure vs. almost-everywhere convergence) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target states the desired subsequence result without building it into the hypotheses) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (the theorem statement is a complete mathematical claim). Notes: implementation will rely on summable exceptional sets and Borel–Cantelli.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Convert convergence in measure into almost-everywhere convergence along a subsequence by shrinking exceptional sets fast enough.\"\n :terms [{:name \"convergence in measure\"\n          :meaning \"For every ε>0 there is N so that n>N implies m{|fₙ-f|>ε} < ε.\"\n          :needed-because \"This provides the quantitative estimate we will use with ε = 1/k.\"}\n         {:name \"summable exceptional sets\"\n          :meaning \"Choose a subsequence so that ∑ m{|f_{n_k}-f|>2^{-k}} < ∞.\"\n          :needed-because \"Summability allows Borel–Cantelli/Fatou arguments to conclude that almost every x falls out of all but finitely many sets.\"}\n         {:name \"diagonal subsequence\"\n          :meaning \"Pick n_k increasing so that the k-th tail estimate holds with ε = 2^{-k}.\"\n          :needed-because \"Constructing the subsequence is the bridge from convergence in measure to almost-everywhere convergence.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"MeasureTheory.convergenceInMeasure_subseq\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Use convergence in measure with ε = 2^{-k} to pick n_k and apply Borel–Cantelli to the sets where |f_{n_k}-f| > 2^{-k}.\"\n             :why-this-now \"This is the standard proof: extract a fast-converging subsequence and rule out infinitely many bad deviations.\"\n             :lean-target \"A Lean lemma stating that convergence in measure implies existence of an a.e.-convergent subsequence.\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has Borel–Cantelli and convergence notions, but the exact lemma may need to be assembled.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"If (fₙ) converges to f in measure on a finite measure space, then some subsequence converges to f almost everywhere.\"\n              :formal-name \"convergence_in_measure_subseq_ae\"\n              :formal-target \"theorem convergence_in_measure_subseq_ae {μ : Measure α} [IsFiniteMeasure μ] {f : α → ℝ} {fₙ : ℕ → α → ℝ} (h : TendstoInMeasure μ fₙ f) : ∃ φ : ℕ → ℕ, StrictMono φ ∧ fₙ ∘ φ ⟶ᵐ[μ] f\"\n              :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                             :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                             :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                             :notes \"Directly states the goal of the exercise, phrased in Lean's measure-theoretic language.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"convergence_in_measure_subseq_ae\"\n               :formal-statement \"Every sequence converging in measure has an a.e.-convergent subsequence.\"\n               :informal-clause \"The main sentence of Stage 1.\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"borel_cantelli_for_subseq\"\n               :formal-statement \"If the measures of the bad sets are summable, then almost every point belongs to only finitely many of them.\"\n               :informal-clause \"Used to show the extracted subsequence converges pointwise almost everywhere.\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n- Stage 1 now contains the full narrative solution (why/key insight/proof/fragility note/what connects) in `execute.md:1-20`.\n- Stage 2 lists the supporting lemmas and how they feed the proof (`execute.md:22-30`), matching `proof-plan.edn`’s strategy entry.\n- Stage 3 explains the Lean blocker (lack of a packaged `convergence_in_measure_subseq_ae` lemma) and Stage 4 records that this sentence remains informal until that API exists (`execute.md:32-44`).\n- `proof-plan.edn` and `formal-alignment.edn` have the required goal/terms/strategy and main-claim/helper alignment, and `changelog.edn` logs workspace init, target-check, Stage 1–2 write-up, and the Stage 3 blocker with the mandated metadata.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A92J02/Apm_v2_a92J02_1775049364123", :frame/id "apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T13:16:04.148565Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A92J02.Apm_v2_a92J02_1775049364123", :proof/problem-id "a92J02", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a92J02/apm-v2-a92J02-1775049364123/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A92J02/Apm_v2_a92J02_1775049364123/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/